defaultRegulatory action
default3.10 In 2012/13, we found seven trusts in significant breach of their terms of Authorisation. This compares with ten in 2011/12 and three in 2010/11. Since 1 April 2013, three trusts have been subject to formal enforcement action under the new licence regime. Additionally, formal enforcement action has been increased at 10 trusts.
default3.11 Five trusts were removed from significant breach during 2012/13: Blackpool Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, Gloucestershire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, James Paget University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, Wirral University Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust and Cambridgeshire and Peterborough NHS Foundation Trust. A number of other foundation trusts could have their enforcement action lifted in the next six to nine months.
default3.12 On 31 October 2013, there were a total of 22 trusts subject to formal regulatory action (see Figure 4); investigations were underway at a further ten trusts to determine whether they were in breach of their licence and whether formal action is required.  
