defaultMaking sure the NHS payment system promotes quality and efficiencydefault4.23 Monitor and NHS England are jointly responsible for the NHS payment system.
default4.24 NHS England decides what services will be bought and if those services should be standardised nationally. We lead on designing the rules  for price setting and calculating the national prices for these services. Collectively, the information, rules and methods that regulate the payment system for NHS services are published in a document called the national tariff.
default4.25 The design of the payment system is important as it can influence the quality of care by, for example:
default4.26 With NHS England we have set out our joint intention to use our shared responsibility for designing the payment system as a means of promoting patients’ interests. In particular, we want to design, test and implement changes to the current system which evidence suggests will ensure quality of care improves continuously for the same or lower costs. We need to use the full breadth of tools available to us as a regulator: from gathering and analysing cost and 
defaultquality data, to creating sharp incentives to change provider and commissioner behaviour for the benefit of patients.
