defaulteg
default, the increase in drugs prices) to ensure some predictability of income for providers while we develop the longer term strategy.
default4.28 However, we have made changes in two important areas for 2014/15 based on our engagement with the sector. Following a review of the marginal rate rule for emergency admissions, we made significant changes to the way baselines and re-investment plans were determined locally, with commissioners held firmly to account for the first time. Local health economies will also be able to adopt alternative payment approaches where this is in patients’ interests, as long as they do so transparently and have engaged constructively on the available options.
